/*
         How to use USB Flash Drive to install Windows 10 in Mac...
         1. Prepare a USB Flash Drive with 16GB's storage at least,which has been already maked into a Windows 10 mode's PE.
         2. Prepare Windows 10.iso and MacOS Mojave.dmg in the USB.
         3. Mac environment:Use bootcamp to get drivers in USB.
         4. Reboot the Mac with 'option'key,then select PE.
         5. Entered PE,free the wasted bootcamp diskpart and recover it to his original place.
         6. Use DISM++x64.exe to install Windows 10.iso file to SSD,select 'add boot' section and format.
         7. Reboot with 'option' key,and select windows,pass through the OOBE without network.
         8. Install the basic drivers by bootcamp's drivers in USB,reboot Windows 10.
         9. Connect to the network to activate Windows and install further drivers and applications,all down!
         
         That's all,and all the tools are available on the Internet,I won't afford here.
         
         */
